Description: Paul Reed Smith CE Custom 24 Electric Guitar in a Whale Blue Finish. This guitar features a Bolt On Pattern Thin Maple Neck, HFS Pickups, Nickel Hardware, Killer Wide & Wavy Flame Top. Paul Reed Smith Case included.Just as nice as the new CE-24's but with a case!It's used and has some minor cosmetic dings. But overall, it's a beauty.Traditional Bolt-on Feel with a Sound all its Own!Since the dawn of rock and roll, the snap and response that comes from a bolt-on neck guitar has been an essential part of the mix. These attributes have, in turn, become essential to many players trying to tell their story through music. The CE 24 brings the bolt-on platform back to the main PRS lineup with some significant updates. The CE 24 pairs PRS's traditional body combination of the mahogany back and maple top with a bolt-on maple neck and rosewood fretboard. The neck sports a Pattern Thin carve and a nice gloss finish. To further maximize the guitar's inherent tone and clarity, the CE 24 features PRS HFS pickups, which Paul designed to have remarkable clarity as well as extended high and low end. The original CE was to introduced in 1988 and offered players PRS design and quality with the added snap and sparkle of traditional bolt-on guitars. NO OVERSEAS SHIPPING!!
